Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Gregory Hughes and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited to have the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.80,0:02:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity to speak to you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.12,0:02:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,today about a super important
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and interesting topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The accessibility of media and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,games.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we strive to surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.47,0:02:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and delight all of our customers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of their abilities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and disabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.09,0:02:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We envision a world where users
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.56,0:02:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,like Patrick are able to do what
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.03,0:02:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they love and love what they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,without being hindered by
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.35,0:02:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.90,0:02:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to make sure that users
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.10,0:02:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with disabilities can experience
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.38,0:02:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the same surprise, delight,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,magic moments and most
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.50,0:02:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,importantly fun when using our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.29,0:02:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As part of that vision, your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.80,0:02:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,apps play a key role.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.57,0:02:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You play such an important part
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.07,0:02:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in helping us to deliver an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.86,0:02:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,inclusive, accessible and fun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.80,0:02:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,platform for all of our users.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:02:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,During our conversations today,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.10,0:03:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,four categories of disabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.34,0:03:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Visual disabilities, which are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,those pertaining to sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.67,0:03:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How much a user can see, in some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.26,0:03:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,cases, the users that can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Motor disabilities, which are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,disabilities pertaining to how a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.30,0:03:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,user interacts physically with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.61,0:03:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the device, whether they can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,hold the device at all, how to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.62,0:03:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,use a keyboard or mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hearing disabilities, which are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.10,0:03:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,those pertaining to how much
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.55,0:03:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody can hear and in some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,cases the complete inability to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.32,0:03:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, disabilities related
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.04,0:03:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to cognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.29,0:03:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are displays that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.74,0:03:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,affect how somebody thinks when
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.25,0:03:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,using your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How much they can remember from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.91,0:03:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the original instructions you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,gave them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what type of UI works best
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.02,0:03:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.29,0:03:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, while talking about these
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.50,0:03:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,disabilities, today we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to break everything down into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.95,0:03:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,three key sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.15,0:03:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'm going to present how
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.69,0:03:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your media and videos
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.11,0:03:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,more accessible in your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.12,0:03:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.07,0:03:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll then build on some of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.24,0:03:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,those topics and talk about how
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.70,0:04:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your games more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.44,0:04:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you think about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible design in gaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is really interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As we talk about this, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,really easy to sit back and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"My game can't be made
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And one thought experiment that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we often go through is let's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.87,0:04:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,start from a point where we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.94,0:04:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,think it can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's assume that somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.37,0:04:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that's blind can use my video
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.17,0:04:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,editing app, or somebody with
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral palsy can play my
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.39,0:04:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,first-person shooter game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The challenge and the fun part
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is then figuring out how that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, try to keep that in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.25,0:04:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as we're going through some of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these specific cases and general
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.09,0:04:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,cases for adding accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.98,0:04:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to your games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.73,0:04:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then last, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,show a demo game that we made,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.74,0:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that highlights some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.27,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible design concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.50,0:04:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll give you some ideas on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.09,0:04:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can implement them in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,your own app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.09,0:04:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first, the accessibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,media and video.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And generally, the most
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.68,0:04:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,straightforward one that people
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:04:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,think about is the accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of images.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyone that's worked in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.38,0:05:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible design will always
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.54,0:05:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,say, always add alt text.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.10,0:05:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not quite that simple
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.43,0:05:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in all cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if we take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.07,0:05:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at this image on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You might describe this as
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"Woman sitting in a hammock
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.93,0:05:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,playing a guitar."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.25,0:05:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An equally good description
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.60,0:05:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,might be "Person playing guitar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.41,0:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with custom artwork drawn using
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a marker."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.23,0:05:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Equally, you could describe this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as "Image demonstrating the use
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.03,0:05:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the camera's aperture to make
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.09,0:05:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the foreground blurry while
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.07,0:05:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping the subject in focus."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.24,0:05:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the important part when
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to describe your images,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to populate that alt
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.00,0:05:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,text, is thinking about how this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,image is used in your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.78,0:05:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.70,0:05:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the context for the image
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.17,0:05:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's it conveying to the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.28,0:05:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,user?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you can think about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.26,0:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you can then create a really
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,good, clear and concise
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,description for users that might
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,not be able to see the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for images we always want
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.21,0:05:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,developers to think about clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.90,0:05:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,concise descriptions that convey
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.10,0:06:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the same information that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.07,0:06:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody, that a sighted user
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,market get.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For audio, we're generally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about disabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.90,0:06:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pertaining to hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How does somebody that can't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hear, or has difficulty hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,perceive the audio in your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.82,0:06:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,application?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.05,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,For audio, there are generally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,two categories of audio that we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,see in apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is spoken audio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And this could be something like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.51,0:06:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a recording of the "I Have a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.60,0:06:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream" speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it could be a podcast that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you play back in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.70,0:06:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But regardless, when dealing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with spoken audio you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,think about in the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your application how can you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,provide somebody that can't hear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.65,0:06:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that spoken audio access to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.49,0:06:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,same information.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is generally some way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.46,0:06:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of providing a transcript.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be a popup that shows
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,up in your app to show a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,transcript.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the case of many great
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.69,0:06:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,podcasts, they have online
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,transcripts that somebody who's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.45,0:06:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,deaf could go and read to get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.05,0:06:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the same contextual information
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.19,0:06:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that is conveyed in the podcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:06:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it really how and why you're
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,using this spoken information
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for how you're going to adapt it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.94,0:07:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to somebody that can't access it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.47,0:07:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,through hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The next way that audio is used
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.83,0:07:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in apps are for sound effects or
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.44,0:07:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ways to convey information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, in a game, you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,might convey where an enemy is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.00,0:07:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,by audio on the left side or the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,right side of the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.39,0:07:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And in these cases, you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,think about how can you provide
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that same information either
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.31,0:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,through visual or haptic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.27,0:07:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again it's thinking about if
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.84,0:07:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody can't hear this audio,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.41,0:07:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,simulate, you can just mute your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,device, how can we convey the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.57,0:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,same information in our game or
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.11,0:07:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,application to such a user.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.22,0:07:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for audio, we are always
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about how to convey the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.94,0:07:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,same information, what is an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.60,0:07:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,alternative way of conveying
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.89,0:07:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.26,0:07:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The last part of media and video
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.25,0:07:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is thinking about video, which
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.83,0:07:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is kind of the combination of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,images and audio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're not familiar,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.62,0:08:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,video has three key tracks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.50,0:08:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes called media groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is a visual track.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.82,0:08:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is kind of the moving
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,pictures that we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.56,0:08:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The next is the audible track.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the track that contains
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.15,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,all the sound, the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,effects, the spoken dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And last is what's called the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.76,0:08:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,legible track.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.04,0:08:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one most people are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.04,0:08:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know most people are familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.51,0:08:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with it because we intro'd this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with a closed-captioned video.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've probably also seen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.51,0:08:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,closed captions in the gym or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.95,0:08:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.00,0:08:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And legible tracks can be more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,than just closed captions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They can also be subtitles for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.56,0:08:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,users that don't understand the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.71,0:08:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They could also be closed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,captions as I said, but another
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,term for closed captions is SDH,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or subtitles for the deaf and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hard of hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles for the deaf and hard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of hearing are different than
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.11,0:08:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,normal subtitles and subtitles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.64,0:08:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,for translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles for the deaf and hard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.29,0:08:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of hearing can include lots more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.09,0:08:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,information about the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.45,0:08:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they might include things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.83,0:09:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,like what song is playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.68,0:09:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there a loud crash in the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.42,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,other room, or in some cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,even the absence of sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.46,0:09:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it will just say silence if
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.38,0:09:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that's important to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.20,0:09:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again it's taking a step
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.92,0:09:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,back and thinking about if I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.48,0:09:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't have the ability to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.75,0:09:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this video, what information
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to be conveyed to such a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, for the most part, this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.77,0:09:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is, you're playing back videos,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's working with your content
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.15,0:09:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,providers and making sure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.71,0:09:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they're aware that you want a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,closed-captioned track created.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And in some cases, a subtitle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,track.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's always thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.44,0:09:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,closed captions and thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,about users with hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.10,0:09:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,impairments and providing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.22,0:09:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.04,0:09:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing this back is really
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.33,0:09:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,simple in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're using AVKit, on iOS or
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,macOS, you don't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.92,0:09:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as your content creator
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,put the track in the video, it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.91,0:09:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will playback appropriately,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.25,0:09:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the user's settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.73,0:09:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're working a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.32,0:09:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,lower level at AVFoundation, you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will need to do a little bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.53,0:09:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,work to let a user select which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.43,0:09:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,captioning track they want to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.72,0:09:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.17,0:10:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're the lower level as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.95,0:10:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I said at the AVFoundation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.14,0:10:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,level, you will need to first
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,get all of the media group for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the legible tracks again, we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.22,0:10:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,said closed captioned subtitles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.03,0:10:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are the legible tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.67,0:10:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll then need to do a little
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.61,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,bit of pruning, because this can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,be a really big list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to exclude forced
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.69,0:10:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,subtitles and auxiliary
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.81,0:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,subtitles from that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.04,0:10:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you' have a final list of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.19,0:10:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the tracks that should be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.38,0:10:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed to a user and you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.75,0:10:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,iterate over them and just add
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.18,0:10:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,them to some kind of menuing, or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of other UI that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.92,0:10:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're displaying to a user.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.78,0:10:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're working even lower
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.03,0:10:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,level than AVFoundation, if
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you're taking responsibility for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,drawing your own video,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rendering each frame, playing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.73,0:10:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,back your audio, you'll also
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.55,0:10:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,then be responsible for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,rendering captioning content.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And depending on what content
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.03,0:10:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you're playing, there can also
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.56,0:10:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,be legal regulations that you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.69,0:10:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,have to honor, system settings
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.66,0:10:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for the user has for how they
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.91,0:10:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,want closed captions to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.10,0:10:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to do this, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,great framework called Media
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.98,0:11:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.13,0:11:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows you to get all
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.49,0:11:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of those user options for things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,like foreground color,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.33,0:11:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,background color, font size,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,font choice and other things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,along those lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.09,0:11:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that you can render captions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the way they look everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.27,0:11:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,else in the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where most people stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.30,0:11:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.75,0:11:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people are aware of closed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.23,0:11:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,captions, they work with their
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.28,0:11:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,content creators.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure they add a captioning
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.55,0:11:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,track.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.82,0:11:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's easy to overlook the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.97,0:11:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,audible track.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.45,0:11:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to say, for somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that can't see, there's already
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.16,0:11:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,audio there, we don't need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.41,0:11:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you think about watching
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.68,0:11:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your favorite movie, or a TV
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.06,0:11:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,show that you watch regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you couldn't see what's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.97,0:11:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,happening, yes, there's audio
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.54,0:11:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but in a lot of cases it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.87,0:11:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,convey everything that's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.65,0:11:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a technology to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.83,0:11:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,solve that and it's called Audio
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Descriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.41,0:11:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a secondary audio
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,track the user can select that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,contains not only all the normal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.89,0:11:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,narration, not only all the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.89,0:12:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,normal speech and sound effects,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but also narration for what's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.55,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now most people have never
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.64,0:12:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I want to play a short clip
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of that intro video, that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.61,0:12:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,includes the audio description
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.23,0:12:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,track.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I have so much that I've
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.06,0:12:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,always wanted to express.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.52,0:12:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm like a volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.08,0:12:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm like Pelee or Mount Etna.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Arm the track for recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm about ready to erupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He dances to a logic session
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as titles appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Designed for Patrick L.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.19,0:12:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Designed for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,An Apple logo appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.72,0:12:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, as you can see, this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.39,0:12:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,audio description track is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,really important for somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that can't see the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.76,0:12:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe not critical in this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.89,0:12:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,short video clip, but it can be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,really important when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.36,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,watching a movie or a TV show to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.76,0:12:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,understand what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.80,0:12:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's mixed correctly with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.49,0:13:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the other audio in the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,video.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.90,0:13:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again the key part here just
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,like captions is working with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.93,0:13:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your content creators to make
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,sure, where appropriate these
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,audio description tracks are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,created and rendered with the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.82,0:13:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,video.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.05,0:13:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing them back, just like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.28,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,captions you will get for free,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as you're using AVKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.13,0:13:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, just like captions if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.85,0:13:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you're working lower level than
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.29,0:13:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,AVKit, at the AVFoundation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.93,0:13:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,level, you'll need to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.39,0:13:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit of work, and almost
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.66,0:13:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the same work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.47,0:13:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,First you'll need to get the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,media group for the audible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.68,0:13:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of pruning this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to look for just the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,track.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.65,0:13:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still pruning but instead
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.85,0:13:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of excluding tracks this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.49,0:13:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to get just the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.32,0:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,primary audio tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.09,0:13:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll then iterate over
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,those to add them to a menu or
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,some other UI where the user can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.80,0:13:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,select them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for video we now have a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.20,0:13:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,complete story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.13,0:13:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We've thought about users who
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.22,0:13:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are blind, users who are deaf
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they interact with our
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.20,0:13:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And how they consume our videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.63,0:14:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we talked about images, make
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.59,0:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,sure you add a clear and concise
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,description to your images.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.34,0:14:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Audio, make sure that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.47,0:14:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,adding an alternative way for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,users to access the audio.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And video, make sure you're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,working with your content
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,creators to create
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,closed-captioned tracks, audio
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.37,0:14:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,description tracks and that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,application will support the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,playback of these correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.57,0:14:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like to hand it over to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,my colleague Charlotte, who's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going to build on some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts and talk about how they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.92,0:14:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can be applied to games and how
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.28,0:14:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make some extraordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.39,0:14:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,games that are accessible to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.95,0:14:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,users with disabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.40,0:14:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.30,0:14:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.32,0:14:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. I'm Charlotte Hill and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.42,0:14:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,today I'm going to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,about accessible games.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When you create a game, you want
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.21,0:14:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to make something that your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.25,0:14:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,users will get lost in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.12,0:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want them to get
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,pulled out of that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.33,0:14:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because of difficulties
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.30,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting with your software.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I'm going to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.24,0:14:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about accessible games and how
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.97,0:14:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a game that's fun to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:14:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,play for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.90,0:15:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, we saw a video of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.15,0:15:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Patrick and how he uses
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver on his iPhone and his
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.18,0:15:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver users like Patrick do
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of things with their
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,phones, including playing games.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.27,0:15:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're developing your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,game, think about VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,users like Patrick with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.37,0:15:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,different abilities and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.55,0:15:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,disabilities and how they'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.04,0:15:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,able to interact with your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.85,0:15:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say I'm designing an app
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the Four in a Row game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.80,0:15:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a two-player game, where
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.54,0:15:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,each player takes turns dropping
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.17,0:15:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,colored tokens into slots on a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.33,0:15:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,vertical 2D gameboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal is to get four of your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tokens in a line and block the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.28,0:15:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,other player from doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.39,0:15:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I design it to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.57,0:15:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible from the ground up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.28,0:15:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.10,0:15:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how I can make my game
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible thinking about four
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.90,0:15:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,areas of accessibility; vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.47,0:15:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,motor, hearing, and cognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,These cover huge spectrum of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,abilities, but we'll focus on
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.31,0:15:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,some key points in each category
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.21,0:15:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they relate to Four in a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.40,0:16:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Row, and likely your game as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.15,0:16:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.06,0:16:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's think about vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.91,0:16:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the context of our game, the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.95,0:16:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,key areas we'll focus on are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.79,0:16:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,color, motion, dynamic type, and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.39,0:16:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver support.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.42,0:16:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the key visual elements
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.69,0:16:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of this game is the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.50,0:16:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiation between the two
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.94,0:16:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,player's tokens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, one player is green and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the other is red.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.88,0:16:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,These colors can be really hard
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.19,0:16:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to distinguish for someone who
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is colorblind, or doesn't see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,color at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.04,0:16:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what the same colors may
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.29,0:16:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,look like to someone who has a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,type of colorblindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at how some
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.36,0:16:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,other apps differentiate without
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,color in their games.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In Causality, the characters are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.24,0:16:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,defined by the colors of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,stripes of their helmets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, take a look at their
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,helmets, and then this is what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:16:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like in the colorblind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.41,0:16:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.47,0:16:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they've added these shapes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.23,0:16:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that go along with the colors to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,help distinguish between the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,characters in their color
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.10,0:17:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,colorblind friendly mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.39,0:17:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We can build off that idea and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,use shapes as well as colors in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.74,0:17:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,our game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.15,0:17:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about how we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,use motion in our game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.14,0:17:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may want to close your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.56,0:17:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes for a second if you get
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.22,0:17:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,motion sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.03,0:17:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is the really cool
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.97,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,animation I wanted to do in the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,background of my game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all distracting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.26,0:17:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it will be a big hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.26,0:17:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,OK you can open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people experience motion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.42,0:17:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sicknesses from these kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.09,0:17:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.30,0:17:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Motion sickness happens when
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.66,0:17:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,some of your senses tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're moving, but others don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.06,0:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're using your phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.43,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your eyes see motion, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,don't feel it in your muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or your inner ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.27,0:17:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Motion sickness from computers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.71,0:17:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually really common.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.06,0:17:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In one study, 70% of adults
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.38,0:17:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,reported motion sickness while
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,playing a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.45,0:17:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In my Four in a Row game, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.84,0:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,make another background with
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.15,0:17:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,less motion to follow the reduce
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,motion setting on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.06,0:17:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't have to be a static
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.38,0:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,image, just tighten up the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.12,0:18:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,physics of the motion so there
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is less motion overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.49,0:18:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can find out more about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,designing for reduce motion on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.96,0:18:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the WebKit blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.36,0:18:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Another accessibility setting to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.81,0:18:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,design for is dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.81,0:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic type or larger text
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes for users with low vision
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lets users go beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,standard text sizes to something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that's easier for them to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.46,0:18:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your game should support the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,standard text sizes as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.47,0:18:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,an accessibility text sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.05,0:18:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which go up to accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,extra, extra, extra-large.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll want to test set out our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.46,0:18:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,game with some different text
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.66,0:18:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes to make sure our layouts
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.93,0:18:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can learn more about making
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.90,0:18:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,your app work with dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.53,0:18:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Dynamic Type Session and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Labs on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.78,0:18:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've done a lot to make our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.72,0:18:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,game more accessible for sighted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,users with vision problems, but
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.59,0:18:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what about low vision or blind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.94,0:18:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,players.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of players may be playing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.58,0:18:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,your game using VoiceOver, the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.25,0:19:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,screen reader that comes built
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.59,0:19:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in on all your Apple devices and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.48,0:19:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,let's players who are blind hear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.06,0:19:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that's on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example of how
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver works.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,On my phone, I'm going to swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,across the screen to move the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.91,0:19:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,different elements and hear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.87,0:19:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver read them to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll tap on the screen and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.19,0:19:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,hear what's under my finger, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.56,0:19:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'll double tap to press an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.01,0:19:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,element, in this case open an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.11,0:19:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Dock, phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, when it's moving through
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.88,0:19:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,those elements you saw the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.81,0:19:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,little square going.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.63,0:19:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It also says what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.01,0:19:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, that way a VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,user can hear everything that's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on their screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.36,0:19:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're using AppKit or UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.72,0:19:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,without a lot of custom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,controls, your game should
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.74,0:19:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,already work pretty well with
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.22,0:19:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do have custom controls
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or images, you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility API to finish
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.83,0:19:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,making your app accessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in my game I have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.26,0:19:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,these tokens that are custom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.48,0:19:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,views.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.23,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want VoiceOver to say the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right thing when it lands on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.68,0:20:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.29,0:20:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go with player A and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.64,0:20:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,player B.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.82,0:20:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can use these strings of the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility label property to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.15,0:20:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,label these elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when VoiceOver lands on a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,token it will say its name
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.72,0:20:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.90,0:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can learn more about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that in the What's New in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Talk that was just
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.35,0:20:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on the screen before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.40,0:20:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be available
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,online and they went into some
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.08,0:20:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,more detail about using the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.21,0:20:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility API.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.58,0:20:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for vision we thought about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,three key points for our Four in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.19,0:20:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Row game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we used shapes and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.99,0:20:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's more than one type
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of indicator for players who are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.03,0:20:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,colorblind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.14,0:20:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We provided alternate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.18,0:20:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences for reduced motion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.88,0:20:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we made sure all of our
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.23,0:20:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,elements were accessible and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,labeled for VoiceOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're designing a game for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.06,0:20:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS or macOS you're usually
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about players swiping
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.32,0:20:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,on a screen or typing on a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.78,0:20:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:20:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However, your players may be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,playing your game using
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,assistive technologies like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Touch Accommodations, the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.52,0:21:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Keyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.07,0:21:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alternative Inputs, and Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.67,0:21:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.62,0:21:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of your players might have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.25,0:21:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulties with fine motor
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.53,0:21:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,skills like from arthritis that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,make it difficult for them to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.19,0:21:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,accurately swipe and tap in your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.36,0:21:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.42,0:21:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,These players may use the Touch
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.72,0:21:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Accommodations and Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings to make it easier for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,them to interact with their
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.84,0:21:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.94,0:21:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's still a good idea
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.39,0:21:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to think about how you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it easier to swipe and tap in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.82,0:21:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.88,0:21:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In my Four in a Row app, players
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.75,0:21:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on a column to drop in their
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.37,0:21:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,token.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.50,0:21:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make sure these
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.42,0:21:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,targets are large and clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,defined, so it's easy for users
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.34,0:21:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to hit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Human Interface Guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,recommends a minimum area of 44
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.29,0:21:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by 44 for topical elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.96,0:21:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're designing a game for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.39,0:21:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,macOS, players might be using
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.29,0:21:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Accessibility Keyboard to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.55,0:21:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,play your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of typing on a physical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.47,0:21:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard, players use the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.08,0:22:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,trackpad, mouse or dwell control
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.14,0:22:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to select keys on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.15,0:22:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Your game should just work with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.27,0:22:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Accessibility Keyboard, but
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.78,0:22:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to provide some
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.01,0:22:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,options for keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.87,0:22:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If your game requires pressing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and releasing multiple keys at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the same time, offer an option
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.17,0:22:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for just pressing a single key
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.47,0:22:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,instead, or allow a press and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,hold so players can use sticky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.09,0:22:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.88,0:22:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear more about the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.53,0:22:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Keyboard in the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's New in Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.11,0:22:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Other players may be playing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.13,0:22:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your game through alternative
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.62,0:22:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,external inputs like braille
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.32,0:22:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,displays, HID controllers, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,external keywords in iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.46,0:22:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,These are great options for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.59,0:22:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,players who have difficulties in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.83,0:22:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,motor skills, or repetitive
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.31,0:22:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,strain injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.28,0:22:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Supporting keyboards for things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,like typing could be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.49,0:22:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,straightforward in your game,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.72,0:22:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may have to do a little
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.86,0:22:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.32,0:22:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in Four in a Row,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.24,0:22:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we needed to implement a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.19,0:22:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,selection mechanism for players
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.90,0:22:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to select a column
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.12,0:22:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,using a keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.65,0:22:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Other players might be playing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.81,0:22:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your game using Switch Control,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.48,0:22:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an assistive technology
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.64,0:23:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,available on macOS, iOS and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.79,0:23:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.08,0:23:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Switch Control lets you control
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.36,0:23:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your device with one or more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.55,0:23:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,switches which are like buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.75,0:23:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be pressed by a hand, a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.23,0:23:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,head, or another body part.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.58,0:23:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're using a single
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.93,0:23:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,switch, Switch Control scans all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,items on screen and then you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.81,0:23:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,tap your switch when it lands on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.20,0:23:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the item you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.81,0:23:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here Switch Control is on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.81,0:23:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's scanning everything in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.04,0:23:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sushi Go, and then when it lands
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.04,0:23:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on my sushi, I tap my switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.44,0:23:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I select my sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.83,0:23:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the good news is that if you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.92,0:23:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,already made your game
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.74,0:23:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible using the accessibly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.69,0:23:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,API for VoiceOver, which is used
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.73,0:23:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by players who are blind, it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.26,0:23:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,should also work with Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.37,0:23:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.37,0:23:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that games like Sushi
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.76,0:23:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Go can be played with just a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.94,0:23:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,single button.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.30,0:23:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In my Four in a Row app, I added
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.73,0:23:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a cool erase gesture that clears
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.58,0:23:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the board when a user swipes in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.06,0:23:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a zigzag.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.15,0:23:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this could be really
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.42,0:23:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult for players who are
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.50,0:23:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,using Switch Control or Touch
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.78,0:23:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Accommodations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.17,0:23:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll put an option on my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.34,0:24:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,settings to use buttons instead
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.08,0:24:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of these gestures, so Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.74,0:24:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,users can use that instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.98,0:24:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When designing for players with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.13,0:24:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulties of motor skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.62,0:24:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to make sure that your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.64,0:24:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,targets are clearly defined and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.39,0:24:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.58,0:24:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to provide for different
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.07,0:24:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,inputs in your game, like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.46,0:24:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,testing it out with Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Control or HID controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.37,0:24:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Provide options for custom
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,gestures so your game is still
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,playable with a single switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.26,0:24:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Players in my game might be deaf
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or hard of hearing and I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.35,0:24:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure they're not missing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.27,0:24:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,out on any of the experience by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.78,0:24:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,providing captions and alert
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,options.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In my Four in a Row game, I want
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.66,0:24:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a single player mode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.92,0:24:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,where the AI speaks taunting
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.33,0:24:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,remarks throughout the game to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.62,0:24:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,increase the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.41,0:24:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However, my players may be deaf
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.10,0:24:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or hard of hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.43,0:24:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Grim Fandango is a complex
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.73,0:24:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,adventure app with a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.97,0:24:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,dialogue, but it lets users pick
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.42,0:24:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between just speech, just text,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.93,0:24:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and speech with text.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.36,0:25:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll use the techniques Greg
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.69,0:25:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,described earlier to add audio
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.41,0:25:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to my game.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.62,0:25:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Settings let your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.89,0:25:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,players customize the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.97,0:25:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,environment to fit their needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.66,0:25:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In Grim Fandango, there's also
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.35,0:25:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,different sliders for adjusting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.02,0:25:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the different types of volume in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.47,0:25:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.81,0:25:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a great option for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.52,0:25:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,players who are hard of hearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.73,0:25:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because that way you can select
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you want your music volume
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.76,0:25:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to be versus what you want the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,volume to be for any speech, for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.76,0:25:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.09,0:25:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on your game, you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.60,0:25:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,might also want to offer sound
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.90,0:25:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,effect options, so players with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.51,0:25:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing loss in one range can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.31,0:25:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,select sound that's in a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.18,0:25:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,different range.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.20,0:25:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In my Four in a Row game, I want
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.03,0:25:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to use sounds that fill the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.09,0:25:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,spectrum, so more people can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.71,0:25:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,hear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.63,0:25:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I also want my sound effects to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.48,0:25:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,be really noticeable for all
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.78,0:25:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,players.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.54,0:25:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll combine them with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.09,0:25:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,screen flashes or haptics on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.74,0:25:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,supported devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.33,0:25:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Deaf or hard of hearing players
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.77,0:25:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,will enjoy your game a lot more
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.36,0:25:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,if you provide captions for any
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.91,0:25:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.19,0:25:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on your sound effects,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.55,0:25:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll want to try to use full
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.63,0:26:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,spectrum sounds, or add audio
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.15,0:26:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,options so players can select
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.69,0:26:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what sounds work best for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.37,0:26:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Try using multiple ways of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.65,0:26:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,getting player's attention, like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.34,0:26:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,screen flashes or haptics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.26,0:26:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of my players might have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.69,0:26:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,cognitive and neurodevelopmental
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.35,0:26:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,disorders like ADHD, autism, or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.06,0:26:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,dementia.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.11,0:26:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These cover a wide spectrum and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.86,0:26:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so it will be really helpful to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.01,0:26:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,get feedback from my users about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.63,0:26:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what challenges they encountered
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.88,0:26:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,while playing Four in a Row.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.59,0:26:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are some key
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.99,0:26:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,areas I can focus on while
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.29,0:26:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,developing my game, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.25,0:26:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,options for audio and visuals,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.14,0:26:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,providing help and tutorials,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.35,0:26:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,supporting Guided Access, and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.22,0:26:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,offering different game modes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.44,0:26:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When we looked at Grim Fandango,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.48,0:26:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,one great option was the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.67,0:26:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of voice and text.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.04,0:26:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great option for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.23,0:26:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,players to comprehend better
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.76,0:26:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when there's a mixture of sound
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.52,0:26:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and visuals in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.62,0:26:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure to provide an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.56,0:26:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,option like that in Four in a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.67,0:26:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Row.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.42,0:26:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing I want to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.24,0:26:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in my game is easy access to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.85,0:26:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.18,0:27:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For players with attention or
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.33,0:27:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,memory problems, it can be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.73,0:27:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,really difficult to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.93,0:27:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,instructions or rules they
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.39,0:27:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,encountered when they first
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.31,0:27:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,played the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.14,0:27:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Solivad [assumed spelling] has a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.88,0:27:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,ton of versions of solitaire and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.60,0:27:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be hard to remember all
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.81,0:27:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,their nuances, but they all have
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.58,0:27:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a rules button available from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.15,0:27:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the same screen where you play
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.23,0:27:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.10,0:27:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do the same thing in Four
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.61,0:27:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in a Row, and add a button to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.82,0:27:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the game playing screen, so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.16,0:27:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,players can get back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.18,0:27:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.59,0:27:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of my players will want to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.54,0:27:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,play my game through Guided
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.71,0:27:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Access.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.77,0:27:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Guided Access offers players
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.34,0:27:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,another way to experience your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.52,0:27:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.66,0:27:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A parent or caretaker can set up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.19,0:27:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,restrictions on the game so the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.90,0:27:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Guided Access user can just
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.34,0:27:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on what's really important
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.79,0:27:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.74,0:27:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in Four in a Row, I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.84,0:27:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have this Auto Play button
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.29,0:27:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a little confusing, it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.95,0:27:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lets the phone play against
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.28,0:27:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,itself and so players who
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.75,0:27:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,stumble across it might not know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.69,0:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened or how to get back
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to just playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.79,0:27:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In Guided Access, a caretaker
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.76,0:27:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,could put a restriction around
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.54,0:27:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that button so that way the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.72,0:27:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Guided Access user can just
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.11,0:27:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy the game without worrying
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.54,0:28:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,about accidentally pressing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.51,0:28:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If your game has things that it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.76,0:28:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would make sense to restrict,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.07,0:28:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use custom restrictions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.14,0:28:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the accessibility API.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These are used in setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.39,0:28:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Guided Access in an app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.71,0:28:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when the player plays
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.45,0:28:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,them, those things are hidden or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.20,0:28:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,locked, so they can't
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.80,0:28:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,accidentally use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.06,0:28:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You may also want to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.04,0:28:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,different modes in your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.83,0:28:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Real Racing has different
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.06,0:28:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,options for drivers that lets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.20,0:28:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,players focus on one aspect of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.73,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the game at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.63,0:28:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on your game it might
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.94,0:28:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,make sense to use different
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.86,0:28:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,levels instead, but you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.53,0:28:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure you're not preventing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.72,0:28:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,players from completing your
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.58,0:28:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.18,0:28:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want Four and a Row to be
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.28,0:28:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,timed, so players really feel
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.85,0:28:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the pressure when making their
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.01,0:28:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,move.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.96,0:28:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a timed version could
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.55,0:28:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be a lot less fun for a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.88,0:28:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,players, including those with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.27,0:28:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cognitive disabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.20,0:28:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll add another option for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.73,0:28:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,an untimed mode in the game as
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.32,0:28:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.90,0:28:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've added leaderboards to Four
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in a Row, but I have to think
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.26,0:29:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about what ranking means to my
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.75,0:29:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,players.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.71,0:29:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have diverse set of players
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.74,0:29:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,playing my game in many
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,different ways, and I don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.11,0:29:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it to feel unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.52,0:29:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll create leaderboards for the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.20,0:29:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,different modes that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.26,0:29:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,play my game in so that way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.92,0:29:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,players in the untimed mode can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.36,0:29:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,compete against each other
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.06,0:29:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,without worrying about what
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.99,0:29:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,times the players in the timed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.22,0:29:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,mode are achieving.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.64,0:29:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Cognitive accessibility covers a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.73,0:29:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,wide range of users, and there's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.33,0:29:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot you can do in your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.91,0:29:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Use multiple methods for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.19,0:29:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,providing content like speech
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.87,0:29:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with captions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.79,0:29:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Make instructions and tutorials
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.31,0:29:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to access while playing the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.73,0:29:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.32,0:29:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Support Guided Access so players
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.59,0:29:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,can focus on just what's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.54,0:29:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,important to enjoy the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.44,0:29:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And offer different game modes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.69,0:29:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or levels, each with their own
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.33,0:29:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,leaderboards, so players can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.79,0:29:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,compete fairly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.89,0:29:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, so now I want to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.04,0:29:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.94,0:29:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings we did in our game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.11,0:29:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I have my game running in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.62,0:29:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the simulator right now with the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.95,0:29:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.06,0:30:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I found the Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.74,0:30:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector in Xcode under
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.12,0:30:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Developer Tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.21,0:30:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a lot you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.50,0:30:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.75,0:30:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm not really going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.69,0:30:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,into it because there's a really
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.81,0:30:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,great talk in it last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.50,0:30:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But over here you can inspect
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.94,0:30:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.40,0:30:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, it will tell you what
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.40,0:30:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,different accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.40,0:30:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,information it can get about the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.94,0:30:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,things in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.44,0:30:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you could run an audit which
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.86,0:30:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is really helpful, because it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.04,0:30:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,will just highlight some
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.99,0:30:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,different accessibility bugs you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.40,0:30:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,might have in your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.25,0:30:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But, today we're going to look
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.15,0:30:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at the settings tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.96,0:30:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is really cool, because
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.12,0:30:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it lets you test different
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.79,0:30:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility settings without
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.19,0:30:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.30,0:30:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just doing this on the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.30,0:30:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator, but up here if you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.18,0:30:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,have your phone plugged in, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.33,0:30:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,can actually pick your phone too
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.01,0:30:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you could do it on device
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.35,0:30:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that way you don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.73,0:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,leave your game and like go into
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.50,0:30:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,settings and go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.40,0:30:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's really handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.78,0:30:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one that we did was reduce
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.67,0:30:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,transparency.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.59,0:30:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that we just did a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.51,0:30:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,simple black background to make
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.15,0:30:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the gameboard really stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.74,0:30:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We also supported different font
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.25,0:30:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes for dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.79,0:30:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a slider here and I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.07,0:30:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,can just make the fonts bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.62,0:30:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.29,0:31:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next one is invert
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.97,0:31:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.45,0:31:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And to know why we implemented
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.47,0:31:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it the way we did, you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.96,0:31:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,know a little bit about how it's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.33,0:31:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,used.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.29,0:31:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, invert colors is used by
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.12,0:31:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,players who have difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.51,0:31:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,reading dark text on a light
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.28,0:31:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,background because the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.04,0:31:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,brightness of the background
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.41,0:31:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,interferes with their vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.98,0:31:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they'll use invert colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.49,0:31:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to make that light text on a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.92,0:31:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,dark background instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.97,0:31:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since our game is already like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.26,0:31:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that, we used the accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.95,0:31:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,API to tell it not to invert
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.50,0:31:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,colors for this screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.07,0:31:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I do invert colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.05,0:31:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.26,0:31:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I go to like settings,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.65,0:31:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is normally white, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.64,0:31:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all black.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.40,0:31:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if I uncheck it, it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.63,0:31:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,goes back to white.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.60,0:31:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a lot of different
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.06,0:31:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,settings here in this game that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.71,0:31:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we added for accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.05,0:31:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.47,0:31:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's check that out as
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.79,0:31:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.50,0:31:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's my Four in a Row app.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.79,0:31:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just tap on a column to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.14,0:31:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.90,0:31:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But more exciting than the game
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.69,0:31:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is the settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.12,0:31:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a lot here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:31:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first is volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.52,0:32:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We added different sliders for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.30,0:32:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the speech and the sound effects
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.65,0:32:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because people who are hard of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.31,0:32:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing might want to emphasize
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.52,0:32:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the speech over the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.59,0:32:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.56,0:32:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we could turn down the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.72,0:32:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.54,0:32:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have captions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.54,0:32:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, those are just going
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.96,0:32:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,directly from the settings for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.31,0:32:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.53,0:32:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have Differentiate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.59,0:32:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Color.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.26,0:32:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you noticed before, right
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.63,0:32:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,now it's all circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.32,0:32:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I turn on Differentiate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.77,0:32:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Colors, we made it so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.27,0:32:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,now it's circles and triangles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.62,0:32:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's easier to tell apart
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.82,0:32:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the different players.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.32,0:32:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a lot of other
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.63,0:32:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,settings here, but the one I
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.95,0:32:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to focus on was timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.05,0:32:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We added a Turn Time slider
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.92,0:32:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is great because that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.34,0:32:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,gives players who have trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.08,0:32:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up their next move or
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.10,0:32:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulty moving that quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.70,0:32:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,some extra time to make their
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.02,0:32:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,move.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.01,0:32:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But for now, I'm going to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.96,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,off the timed mode because I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be testing this out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.07,0:32:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with some assistive technologies
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.00,0:32:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the combination me using
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.63,0:32:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,them and talking about them is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.65,0:32:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,going to slow me down a little
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.53,0:32:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.41,0:33:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, oh, yeah and I'm already
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.54,0:33:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,very close to losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.74,0:33:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm glad I turned that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.16,0:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so now I'm going to test
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.69,0:33:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it out with VoiceOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.53,0:33:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have VoiceOver set up on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.17,0:33:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,my accessibility shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.89,0:33:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can just triple tap on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.37,0:33:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,home and turn on voice over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.06,0:33:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,>> VoiceOver on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.09,0:33:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.79,0:33:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Four in a Row.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.74,0:33:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Empty image.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.73,0:33:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, it's labelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.12,0:33:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.54,0:33:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can swipe through and hear
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.40,0:33:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all the cells in the gameboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.81,0:33:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Move empty image, empty
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.66,0:33:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,image, empty image.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.11,0:33:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Winner, four question marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.17,0:33:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Actions of player B, image.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.96,0:33:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Player B image.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.97,0:33:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Actions available.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.62,0:33:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I can move to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.81,0:33:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's labelled, it's accessible,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.43,0:33:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I was testing this out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.75,0:33:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier in VoiceOver, I found it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.57,0:33:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just wasn't a really fun
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.78,0:33:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.33,0:33:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was too hard to move through
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.36,0:33:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all the different slots on the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.77,0:33:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,gameboard, keep track in your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.86,0:33:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,head of which ones were filled
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.94,0:33:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and which weren't and come up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.97,0:33:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with what your next move should
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.56,0:33:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.65,0:34:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I used something in the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.12,0:34:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility API called the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.64,0:34:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Custom Action to improve that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.22,0:34:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.35,0:34:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I added an action that switches
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.85,0:34:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you from moving by cell to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.31,0:34:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,moving by column.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.67,0:34:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.36,0:34:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Move by cell, move by column.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.79,0:34:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Column 3, 4 empty cells, 2
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.61,0:34:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,player A tokens.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.78,0:34:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, that way VoiceOver can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.26,0:34:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,move via column instead of by
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.61,0:34:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,cell and that makes it a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.38,0:34:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,easier for me to just get a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.64,0:34:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of what the gameboard is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.12,0:34:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that technique I used for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.27,0:34:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,making it move by column instead
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.22,0:34:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of by cell was also really
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.52,0:34:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful for Switch Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.64,0:34:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me show you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.69,0:34:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to turn off VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.28,0:34:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and switch over to Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.31,0:34:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.84,0:34:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Alert. Accessibility list
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.69,0:34:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,control button.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.15,0:34:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.43,0:34:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,>> OK, so now I have Switch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.41,0:34:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Control on and I have my switch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.85,0:34:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.78,0:34:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And Switch Control is scanning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.82,0:34:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.13,0:34:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Switch Control is scanning all
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.32,0:34:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the items on the screen and so
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.88,0:35:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when I go into the gameboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to, before it was
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.24,0:35:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going by cell, and it was super
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.24,0:35:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,tedious to try to wait for it to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.83,0:35:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,go through each cell to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.54,0:35:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.03,0:35:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, when I go into the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.13,0:35:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,gameboard, it's going by column
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.56,0:35:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of by cell, which it did
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.73,0:35:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,originally, and so I was able to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.88,0:35:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,use accessibility API to change
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.52,0:35:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience to make it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.57,0:35:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.32,0:35:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I can just press my
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.70,0:35:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,switch and make my move.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.54,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me show you some other
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.26,0:35:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,things that we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.80,0:35:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me turn off Switch Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.83,0:35:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And right now, if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.99,0:35:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,noticing I have my screen setup
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.99,0:35:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a switch too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.04,0:35:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's an awesome option for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.06,0:35:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,testing, because that way you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.09,0:35:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't need to set up a switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.52,0:35:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're just, your phone
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.72,0:35:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,works as a switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.40,0:35:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we also made it work
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.45,0:35:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with a keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.09,0:35:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I mentioned earlier for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.23,0:35:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you needed to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.41,0:35:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,selection mechanism, so that way
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.36,0:35:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when I hit the arrow keys, I can
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.59,0:35:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,move by column, and then just
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.26,0:35:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,press space to make my move.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.00,0:36:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, providing these options for
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.74,0:36:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,these different assistive
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.73,0:36:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,technologies really broadens
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.04,0:36:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,into my audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.84,0:36:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It means a lot more people will
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.96,0:36:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to play our game.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.79,0:36:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We were able to make a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.58,0:36:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to our game by
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.77,0:36:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,testing it out with different
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.90,0:36:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,assistive technologies and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.14,0:36:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.22,0:36:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're doing this, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.12,0:36:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,be easy to fall into the trap of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.69,0:36:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,following the letter of the law,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.12,0:36:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but not the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.53,0:36:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as being accessible, you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.19,0:36:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,want your game to be fun to play
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.47,0:36:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.11,0:36:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The accessibility API offers a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.83,0:36:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of great tools for improving
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.26,0:36:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.70,0:36:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may be thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.04,0:36:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your own app and how you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.70,0:36:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,started making it accessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.67,0:36:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The three things you can do the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.93,0:36:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,minute you walk out of here are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.56,0:36:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to audit your app, test it out
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.70,0:36:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with different accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.76,0:36:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,settings, and most importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.86,0:36:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to assistive technology
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.20,0:36:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we already mentioned this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.02,0:36:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a little bit, but it's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.99,0:36:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.56,0:36:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can learn more about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.46,0:36:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,both auditing your app and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.77,0:36:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,testing it with accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.91,0:36:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,settings and Auditing your Apps
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.75,0:37:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for Accessibility talk from last
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.30,0:37:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.04,0:37:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really important to test
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.92,0:37:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,out your game with assistive
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.26,0:37:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,technologies, but you should
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.65,0:37:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,also try to talk to the users
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.13,0:37:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who use them every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.81,0:37:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have a firsthand
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.70,0:37:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of what separates a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.04,0:37:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,good experience from a great
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.45,0:37:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.88,0:37:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll probably have a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.32,0:37:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of ideas for how you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.65,0:37:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your game more accessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.46,0:37:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can connect with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.37,0:37:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility users and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.67,0:37:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,developers at our get-together
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.14,0:37:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.70,0:37:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Designing your game for
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.62,0:37:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility really means more
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.30,0:37:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,people can enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.72,0:37:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're designing for
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.03,0:37:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility think about how
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.34,0:37:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility is really a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.62,0:37:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.39,0:37:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you want to create these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.64,0:37:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,different great experiences so
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.50,0:37:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,each player can find out their
